cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with understanding CNNs for text classification. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the inner workings of CNNs and their behavior in processing text. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with neural networks and their application in natural language processing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper draws comparisons between CNNs used in computer vision and those used for text. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper deals with text classification and prediction interpretability.
